issue.title: Option to getHTML() without creating outer <span>
issue.body:
Ideally I'd like to reduce the amount of DOM I have in React by not having the outer span appended. ```tsx const value = 'VALUE' return (
{intl.getHTML('key', { value }).d({value} Look at that cool value!)}
) ``` Currently results in: ```html
VALUE Look at that cool value!
``` What I would prefer: ```html
VALUE Look at that cool value!
``` Also using an empty outer tag breaks it entirely: ```tsx const value = 'VALUE' return (
{intl.getHTML('key', { value }).d(<>{value} Empty tag for smaller DOM but it breaks)}
) ``` ```html
<>VALUE Empty tag for smaller DOM but it breaks
``` I would want it to result in this: ```html
VALUE Empty tag for smaller DOM but it breaks
```

comment.body:
Yes, currently an outer `<span>` will be added to the message. It will be a break change if `<span>` was removed. 
So I prefer to remain current behavior.

comment.body:
I give up using `umi.js@4` since it doesn't support SSG (Static Site Generation).
[Next.js](https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/data-fetching/get-static-paths) would be one of the alternatives.

VALUE Look at that cool value!
``` Also using an empty outer tag breaks it entirely: ```tsx const value = 'VALUE' return (
{intl.getHTML('key', { value }).d(<>{value} Empty tag for smaller DOM but it breaks)}
) ``` ```html
<>VALUE Empty tag for smaller DOM but it breaks
``` I would want it to result in this: ```html
VALUE Empty tag for smaller DOM but it breaks
```

comment.body:
Yes, currently an outer `<span>` will be added to the message. It will be a break change if `<span>` was removed. 
So I prefer to remain current behavior.

comment.body:
I give up using `umi.js@4` since it doesn't support SSG (Static Site Generation).
[Next.js](https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/data-fetching/get-static-paths) would be one of the alternatives.
